# digiquant-atlas — System Overview

## Purpose
Daily market intelligence system using a **9-phase** AI-orchestrated pipeline. **Supabase-first**: canonical state lives in `daily_snapshots` and `documents` tables. Markdown is derived for display.

## 9-Phase Pipeline
| Phase | Name | Skill File |
|-------|------|-----------|
| 1 | Alternative Data | `skills/premarket-pulse/SKILL.md` + alt-data skills |
| 2 | Institutional Intel | `skills/inst-institutional-flows/SKILL.md` + hedge-fund skill |
| 3 | Macro Regime | `skills/macro/SKILL.md` |
| 4 | Asset Classes | bonds / commodities / forex / crypto / intl skills |
| 5 | Equities + Sectors | `skills/equity/SKILL.md` + 11 sector skills |
| 6 | Earnings & Events | `skills/earnings/SKILL.md` |
| 7 | Digest Synthesis | `skills/orchestrator/SKILL.md` Phase 7 |
| 8 | Portfolio Layer | deliberation → PM → rebalance |
| 9 | Evolution | post-mortem + proposals |

## Critical Files
- `skills/orchestrator/SKILL.md` — read this FIRST for any full session
- `config/watchlist.md` — tracked assets
- `config/preferences.md` — trading style + active theses
- `AGENTS.md` — cross-platform behavioral rules

## Web Fetch Protocol
When following any URL to read an article, news page, speech, or filing:
```bash
defuddle parse <url> --md   # strips nav/ads/clutter before reading
```
Do NOT use defuddle for `.md` files, `.json` endpoints, or Supabase/API URLs — use WebFetch directly.

## Token Mode Protocol
- **Caveman ON** (terse) for: phase announcements, triage decisions, checkpoints, inter-phase reasoning
- **Normal mode** for: any content publishing to Supabase — narratives, rationale fields, recommendations
- Switch: say `normal mode` before authoring DB content, `caveman mode` after publishing

## Research Library
Two-tier knowledge base:
- **Tier 1** — Quick-reference summary in `docs/research/LIBRARY.md`; full papers in Supabase under `research/papers/*` (7 doctrine papers)
- **Tier 2** — Dynamic deep dives, concepts, themes in Supabase `documents` (`document_key: research/deep-dives/*`, `research/concepts/*`)

```bash
python3 scripts/fetch_research_library.py             # index
python3 scripts/fetch_research_library.py --ticker X  # filter
python3 scripts/publish_research.py --key research/deep-dives/X-DATE --title "..." --type deep-dive --content -
```

## Behavioral Rules
- **Always** read `config/` files at session start
- **Always** query Supabase `daily_snapshots` for prior context before each phase
- **Never** hand-edit canonical rows in Supabase; use `publish_document.py` / `materialize_snapshot.py`
- **Never** treat `data/agent-cache/` scratch as source of truth — Supabase is canonical
- macOS sed: use `sed -i ""` NOT `sed -i`
